d is part of the [[Southwest Finland]] [[regions of Finland|region]]. The municipality had a population of 6,026 (2004-12-31) and covered an area of 407.79&nbsp;km\u00b2 (excluding sea) of which 9.91&nbsp;km\u00b2 is inland water. The [[population density]] was 15.15 inhabitants per km\u00b2.\n\nThe municipality was unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n*http://www.pernio.fi/ \u2013 Official website {{in lang|fi}}\n\n{{coord|60|12|15|N|23|07|20|E|region:FI_type:city(6026)_scale:50000|display=title}}\n\n{{FinlandProper}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pernio}}\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Finland]]\n[[Category:Salo, Finland]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2009]]\n[[Category:2009 disestablishments in Finland]]\n\n\n{{WesternFinland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = Perni\u00f6\n| official_name           = {{lang|fi|Perni\u00f6n kunta}}<br />{{lang|sv|Bj\u00e4rn\u00e5 kommun}}\n| native_name             = Perni\u00f6 \u2013 Bj\u00e4rn\u00e5\n| native_name_lang        = <!-- ISO 639-2 code. If more than one, use {{lang}} instead  -->\n| settlement_type         = [[Municipalities of Finland|Former municipality]]\n| image_skyline           = Perni\u00f6n kirkko1.jpg\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Perni\u00f6 church\n| image_flag              = \n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = \n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = Perni\u00f6.vaakuna.svg\n| shield_alt              = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = Perni\u00f6.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = <!-- Finland -->\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption  