ication|Climate]]\n| blank3_info             = [[Humid continental climate#Mild/cool summer subtype|Dfb]]\n| timezone                = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n| utc_offset              = +2\n| timezone_DST            = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST          = +3\n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          = \n| area_code               = \n| website                 = http://www.pernio.fi/\n| footnotes               = \n}}\n\n'''Perni\u00f6''' ({{IPA-fi|\u02c8perni\u00f8}}; {{lang-sv|Bj\u00e4rn\u00e5}}) is a [[list of former municipalities of Finland|former municipality]] of [[Finland]]. It was consolidated with [[Salo, Finland|Salo]] on January 1, 2009.\n\nIt is located in the [[provinces of Finland|province]] of [[Western Finland]] and is part of the [[Southwest Finland]] [[regions of Finland|region]]. The municipality had a population of 6,026 (2004-12-31) and covered an area of 407.79&nbsp;km\u00b2 (excluding sea) of which 9.91&nbsp;km\u00b2 is inland water. The [[population density]] was 15.15 inhabitants per km\u00b2.\n\nThe municipality was unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat-inline}}\n*http://www.pernio.fi/ \u2013 Official website {{in lang|fi}}\n\n{{coord|60|12|15|N|23|07|20|E|region:FI_type:city(6026)_scale:50000|display=title}}\n\n{{FinlandProper}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pernio}}\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Finland]]\n[[Category:Salo, Finland]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2009]]\n[[Category:2009 disestablishments in Finland]]\n{{WesternFinland-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perni%C3%B6"}
{"title_page": "Pargas (former municipality)", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Pargas\n|official_name          = {{lang|sv|Pargas stad}}<br />{{lang|fi|Paraisten kaupunki}}\n|native_name            = {{lang|sv|Pargas}} \u2013 {{lang|fi|Parainen}}\n|settlement_type        = Former town\n|image_skyline          = Parainen kirkonkyl\u00e4.JPG\n|image_shield           = Parainen vaakuna.svg\n|image_map              = Parainen.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = 150px\n|map_caption            = Location of Pargas in Finland\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 150px\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Finland]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of Finland|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Southwest Finland]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Sub-regions of Finland|Sub-region]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[\u00c5boland]]\n|leader_title           = [[City manager]]\n|leader_name            = Folke \u00d6hman\n|established_title      = [[Charter]]\n|established_date       = 1948\n|established_title2     = [[Town privileges]]\n|established_date2      = 1977\n|extinct_title          = Consolidated\n|extinct_date           = 2009\n|area_footnotes         = <ref name=\"total area\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.maanmittauslaitos.fi/sites/default/files/pinta_alat_kunnittain_01012008.pdf |title= Area by municipality as of {{#time: j F Y|2008-01-01}} |accessdate={{#time: j F Y|2010-04-13}} |publisher= Land Survey of Finland |format= PDF |language= Finnish, Swedish}}</ref>\n|area_total_km2         = 476.73\n|area_land_km2          = 273.18\n|area_water_km2         = 203.55\n|population_as_of       = 2008-12-31\n|population_footnotes   = <ref name=\"population count\">{{Cite web |url= http://vrk.fi/default.aspx?docid=786&site=3&id=0 |title= Population by municipality as of {{#time: j F Y|2008-12-31}} |accessdate= {{#time: j F Y|2011-01-20}} |work= Population Information System |publisher= Population Register Center of Finland |language= Finnish, Swedish |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110720194510/http://vrk.fi/default.aspx?docid=786&site=3&id=0 |archivedate= 2011-07-20 }}</ref>\n|population_total       = 12266\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|demographics_type1             = [[Languages of Finland|Population by native language]]\n|demographics1_title1           = [[Finnish language|Finnish]]\n|demographics1_info1            = 45% (official)\n|demographics1_title2           = [[Finland Swedish|Swedish]]\n|demographics1_info2            = 54% (official)\n|demographics1_info3            = % \n|demographics1_info4            = %\n|demographics2_title1           = 0 to 14\n|demographics2_info1            = %\n|demographics2_title2           = 15 to 64\n|demographics2_info2            = %\n|demographics2_title3           = 65 or older\n|demographics2_info3            = %\n|timezone               = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n|utc_offset             = +2\n|timezone_DST           = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +3\n|coordinates            = {{coord|60|18|N|022|18|E|region:FI|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type       = Postal code\n}}\n\n'''Pargas''' ({{IPA-sv|\u02c8p\u0251r\u02d0\u0261\u0251s|langfi}}; {{lang-fi|Parainen}}, {{IPA-fi|\u02c8p\u0251r\u0251i\u032fnen|pron}}) is a former [[List of cities and towns in Finland|town]] and [[List of former municipalities of Finland|municipality]] in south-western Finland. On 1 January 2009, it was consolidated with [[Houtsk\u00e4r]], [[Ini\u00f6]], [[Korpo]] and [[Nagu, Finland|Nagu]] to form the new municipality of [[V\u00e4st\u00e5boland]] (since renamed to ''[[Pargas]]'').\n\nIt is known as the \"capital\" of the archipelago of Turku and had been called a town since 1977. It is located in the [[provinces of Finland|province]] of [[Western Finland]] and is part of the [[Southwest Finland]] [[regions of Finland|region]]. The town had a population of 12,266 (as of 31 December 2008)<ref name=\"population count\" /> and covered a land area of {{convert|273.18|km2|sqmi}}.<ref name=\"total area\" /> The [[population density]] was {{convert|44.9|PD/km2}}.\n\nThe municipality was [[bilingual]], with the majority (54%) being [[Swedish language|Swedish]] and the minority (45%) [[Finnish language|Finnish]] speakers.\n\nThe city has many little suburbs around it, including Kirjala and Lielax.\n[[Image:Airisto, Parainen, Finland-a.jpg|thumb|left|280px|View from Airisto harbour, Storm\u00e4l\u00f6]]\n\n==International relations==\n{{Main|List of twin towns and sister cities in Finland}}\n\n===Twin towns \u2014 Sister cities===\nThe sister cities of Pargas are\n\n* {{flagicon|Sweden}} [[Haninge Municipality|Haninge]], Sweden\n* {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Ulstein]], Norway\n* {{flagicon|Russia}} [[Chudovo, Chudovsky District, Novgorod Oblast|Chudovo]], Russia\n* {{flagicon|Estonia}} [[K\u00e4rdla]], Estonia\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{commons category-inline|Pargas}}\n* {{wikivoyage-inline|Pargas}}\n* [http://www.pargas.fi/ Official website] \u2013 in Swedish and Finnish\n\n{{FinlandProper}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2009]]\n[[Category:2009 disestablishments in Finland]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in Finland]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Finland]]\n[[Category:Pargas]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Pargas\n|official_name          = {{lang|sv|Pargas stad}}<br />{{lang|fi|Paraisten kaupunki}}\n|native_name            = {{lang|sv|Pargas}} \u2013 {{lang|fi|Parainen}}\n|settlement_type        = Former town\n|image_skyline          = Parainen kirkonkyl\u00e4.JPG\n|image_shield           = Parainen vaakuna.svg\n|image_map              = Parainen.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = 150px\n|map_caption            = Location of Pargas in Finland\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 150px\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|sub